title: "MDE Candles v2 — Diagram downloads"
---

## Diagram downloads

Three Excalidraw source files accompany the Candles v2 design (parent page: [Market Data Engine — Candles v2](#)). They live in the `market-data-engine` repo at `docs/diagrams/` and render in any Excalidraw client.

### How to view / export

1. Open [excalidraw.com](https://excalidraw.com) (or the VS Code Excalidraw plugin).
2. File → Open → pick the `.excalidraw` file from your local clone of `market-data-engine`.
3. Export as PNG / SVG from the same menu if you need a static image.

No `git clone` needed if you only want to view — grab the raw file from Bitbucket:

```
https://bitbucket.org/paytmteam/market-data-engine/raw/develop/docs/diagrams/{filename}
```

### Files

| # | File | What it shows |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | `mde-v2-architecture.excalidraw` | End-to-end MDE v2 component diagram: feed → `candle-writer` → Redis / ClickHouse → `charts-api` → PML UI. Dual-sink writer, running-candles cache, source-switch logic. |
| 2 | `mde-v2-flow.excalidraw` | Request / data flow: tick ingestion, running-candle updates, 1m close-out, the three `charts-api` read surfaces. |
| 3 | `mde-v2-flowcharts.excalidraw` | Decision flowcharts: source selection, fault-tolerant writer logic, rollback paths. |

### Repo paths

- `market-data-engine/docs/diagrams/mde-v2-architecture.excalidraw`
- `market-data-engine/docs/diagrams/mde-v2-flow.excalidraw`
- `market-data-engine/docs/diagrams/mde-v2-flowcharts.excalidraw`

### Note on Confluence attachments

These are source files, not PNG exports. They are **not attached to this Confluence page** — Confluence attachment upload needs a personal API token which was not available at authoring time. If you would like native attachments (so you can download without touching the repo), ping `girish3.kumar@paytm.com` and a follow-up will upload them via the REST v1 `/content/{id}/child/attachment` endpoint.
